    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 factors. Seven factors were assessed with achieved levels below required levels across all seven; six factors were not assessed and flagged as epistemic gaps at Model Risk Level 5. The primary hemolysis prediction claim appears well-supported by the ValidationResult nodes documenting PIV comparison, in-vitro hemolysis comparison, GCI study, and Monte Carlo UQ, each with full provenance to experimental evidence. On the basis of the documented validation activities and the richly described claim regarding absolute HI prediction adequacy, the assessment team accepted the package as structurally complete for submission, noting that credibility factor gaps will require remediation prior to regulatory decision.",
